  <main class="wrap">
    <h1>2025 Theme : Kaigalil Deivam – The Divine in Everyday Hands</h1>

    <p>As you walk past the rows of Gods in this Golu, pause here — to see the everyday divine.<br>
    These dolls tell the stories of artisans, farmers, musicians, and cooks.<br>
    Their hands, though ordinary, carry extraordinary grace.</p>

    <h2>கைவினையாளர் (Kaivinaialar) – The Artisans</h2>
    <p>At the center, women shaping food, men crafting, dancers in rhythm.<br>
    From grand silk weavers to a mother’s ladle stirring thair saadam, artistry lives in every palm.<br>
    ✨ Here, creation itself is worship.</p>

    <h2>உழவர் (Uzhavar) – The Farmers</h2>
    <p>Figures bent in harvest, sowing and reaping.<br>
    The quiet ones who turn soil into gold — not wealth, but sustenance.<br>
    Every handful of rice carries their devotion.<br>
    🌱 They are the heartbeat of our plates.</p>

    <h2>இசைக்கலைஞர் (Isaikkalainjar) – The Musicians</h2>
    <p>Instruments in hand, songs in air.<br>
    Their craft uplifts, carrying the divine in melody.<br>
    Every note is a bridge — from the mundane to the sacred.<br>
    🎶 In their rhythm, devotion dances.</p>

    <h2>அன்னதானம் (Annadhana) – The Cooks</h2>
    <p>Bowls of rice, fruits, and ladles at rest.<br>
    Food is not mere nourishment, it is offering.<br>
    From the hearth to the feast, cooking is prayer in motion.<br>
    🍲 Here, hunger meets grace.</p>

